This picture certainly gives pause for thought.  For instance, is this a FOOD inspection?  Or are the men lining up to complain about the food with  statements such 'I'm not eating THIS s...t!&quot;
The fellow standing with his fist on his waist behind the chap in the leather coat looks like a tough forman who is going to give them something to complain ABOUT afterwards, he is in the kind of stance and with the look on his face that one would see on a sergeants face.
Then again, it is very early in the morning here in New Zealand, brain is sluggish, imagination is non existant and for all I know they are lining up to say something like &quot; Thank you for the delightfull breakfast sir, may we have more and perhaps some to take home?&quot; 
.

&quot;Waiter, I've just found a fly in my soup!&quot;

&quot;What do you expect ME to do, throw it a lifebelt?&quot;

Sorry, but it IS near Christmas, the silly season.
